# Docstrings: Include Module Docstring

When you improve, add, or review docstrings in a Python file, **also consider the
module docstring** (the string at the top of the file).

Do not skip it by default. If the module docstring is missing or minimal (e.g.
only a title), add or extend it with a single-sentence summary of the module’s
purpose. **Use the format in `module-docstring-format.mdc`**: title line, `=`
underline, blank line, then description. Apply the same docstring style rules
(capitalisation, line length) as for functions and classes.

## Example

```python
# minimal — consider improving
"""
mypackage._config
================
"""

# improved — one-sentence summary of what the module does
"""
mypackage._config
================

Config dataclasses and loading from pyproject.toml and the CLI.
"""
```
